President Donald Trump announced that three more states will begin a phased reopening process on May 1 after meeting the requirements for decreasing cases of COVID-19.
The governors of Ohio, North Dakota and Idaho all intend to begin the process.
(RELATED: US Ramps Up Crackdown On Chinaâ€™s Spying Efforts During Coronavirus)Phase one allows restaurants, gyms, movie theaters and churches to reopen so long as they follow distancing guidelines.
Phase three allows major sporting events to return under light distancing guidelines, and employers can return to normal staffing.
The decision to begin the reopening process ultimately lies with individual governors, according to Trump.